data.enText: an officer of the highest rank in the British army or air force
Marshal of the Royal Air Force
a person responsible for making sure that public events, especially sports events, take place without any problems, and for controlling crowds
(in the US) an officer whose job is to put court orders into effect

data.chText: （一些美国城市的）警察局长，消防局长
data.enText: (in some US cities) an officer of high rank in a police or fire department
to gather together and organize the people, things, ideas, etc. that you need for a particular purpose

data.chText: 他们已经开始结集队伍将救济物资送给遭受飓风侵害的灾民。
data.enText: They have begun marshalling forces to send relief to the hurricane victims.

data.chText: 整理你的论点 / 想法 / 论据
控制人群；组织；维持秩序
data.enText: to control or organize a large group of people
Police were brought in to marshal the crowd.

tr: a law officer having duties similar to those of a sheriff in carrying out the judgments of a court of law
(in some countries) a military officer of highest rank
make ready for action or use
lead ceremoniously, as in a procession

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 marshaling, mar-shaled

value.def: If you marshal people or things, you gather them together and arrange them for a particular purpose.

example.ex: Richard was marshalling the doctors and nurses, showing them where to go.
example.tran: 理查德正在召集医护人员，向他们说明去哪里。

example.ex: ...the way in which Britain marshalled its economic and political resources to protect its security interests.
example.tran: 英国为保护其安全利益所采取的集中经济与政治资源的方法

value.def: A marshal is an official who helps to supervise a public event, especially a sports event.

example.ex: The grand prix is controlled by well-trained marshals...
example.tran: 大奖赛由训练有素的典礼官协调指挥。

example.ex: During the demonstration, marshals handed over to the police a young man caught breaking shop windows.
example.tran: 游行示威期间，组织者逮到一个正在砸商店玻璃的年轻人并将其移送警方。

value.tran: 司仪，典礼官；(尤指体育赛事的)总指挥

value.def: In the United States and some other countries, a marshal is a police officer, often one who is responsible for a particular area.

example.ex: A federal marshal was killed in a shoot-out.
example.tran: 枪战中一名联邦警察局局长身亡。

value.def: A marshal is an officer in a fire department.

example.tran: 克利夫兰县的消防队长

value.def: In Britain and some other countries, a marshal is an officer who has the highest rank in an army or air force.

example.tran: 空军上将肯尼思·克罗斯爵士

value.tran: (英国等的)陆军元帅，空军元帅
